definition3: a recording of a performance, piece of music, speech etc on tape
definition4: a special plastic box containing a length of tape that you can record sound and pictures on, videotape
definition5: a special plastic box containing a length of tape that you can record sound on, cassette
definition6: a string stretched out across the finishing line in a race and broken by the winner
definition7: a tape measure
definition8: narrow length of sticky material used to stick things together, sellotape BrE , scotch tape AmE
definition9: narrow plastic material covered with a special magnetic substance, on which sounds, pictures, or computer information can be recorded and played
definition10: thin plastic in a long narrow strip with a magnetic covering which allows sounds or sounds and pictures to be recorded and played again, or a cassette, especially one on which sound is (to be) recorded
